HEADWORD: Orrery
<hw>Or"re*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Orreries</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[So named in honor of the
Earl of <etsep>Orrery</etsep>.]</ety> <def>An apparatus which
illustrates, by the revolution of balls moved by wheelwork, the relative
size, periodic motions, positions, orbits, etc., of bodies in the solar
system.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

